Desert Island Discs: Tom Daley ya ji 'ba shi da aiki' domin yanayinsa
Mai tseren ruwa na Olympics Tom Daley ya ce ya girma yana jin cewa ba shi da amfani ga kowa domin yanayinsa na jima'i - amma hakan ya ƙarfafa shi ya yi wani abu a duniya.
Wani ɗan shekara 24 bai san cewa "waɗansu mutane ba su da wayo" ba sai da ya shiga makarantar sakandare.
A wani jawabi da ya yi a shirin farko na Rediyo 4 Desert Island Discs da Lauren Laverne ta yi, ya ce yana magana ne game da 'yancin aure don ya ba su "bege".
Ya kuma ce yin tsere ya taimaka masa ya rage alhini game da nasararsa a gasar Olympics.
Kirsty Young, wadda take gudanar da wannan tattaunawar mai tsawo, ta yi hutu na wata ɗaya don rashin lafiya.
Da yake kamar wanda ba shi da aiki a shirin Laverne na farko, Daley ya ce ya ji "ƙanƙantacce" a lokacin da yake girma domin "ba a yarda da shi ba a cikin al'umma don sha'awar maza da mata".
Ya ce: "Har wa yau, wannan halin na rashin mutunci da na daraja kaina ne yake ƙarfafa ni in yi wani abu a duniya".
Ya ce yana son ya tabbatar da cewa shi ma "yana nan", don kada wasu su ji kunya sa'ad da suka san wani abu game da halittunsa.
Dan wasan da ya lashe lambar tagulla ta Olympics sau biyu ya zama sanannen sanannen gay a cikin al'ummomin LGBT kuma ya yi amfani da bayyanarsa a wasannin Commonwealth na wannan shekara a Ostiraliya don neman sauran ƙasashe su ɗaga takunkumin da aka sanya wa ma'aurata marasa aure.
Ya ce yana farin ciki cewa yana da 'yanci kuma yana son ya sa wasu su kasance da "bege".
Wani ɗan wasa da ya lashe gasar cin kofin duniya sau uku ya ce ya yi soyayya da wani saurayi - wani ɗan fim a Amirka mai suna Dustin Lance Black, wanda ya sadu da shi a shekara ta 2013 - kuma ya "burge ni".
Daley ta auri wani ɗan wasan da ya yi nasara a gasar Oscar, wanda ya girme ta da shekara 20 a wannan shekarar, amma ta ce ba ta damu da bambancin shekarunsu ba.
"Idan ka fuskanci irin wannan bala'in a lokacin ƙuruciyarka" - ya halarci gasar Olympics sa'ad da yake ɗan shekara 14 kuma mahaifinsa ya mutu shekara uku bayan haka - ya ce yana da wuya a sami wani a lokacin da ya fuskanci irin wannan bala'in, mai kyau da marar kyau.
A watan Yuni, ma'auratan sun haifi ɗa mai suna Robert Ray Black-Daley, kuma Daley ya ce "dukkan ra'ayinsa" sun canja.
"Idan ka tambaye ni a bara, amsar da na ba ka ita ce, 'Ina son na lashe zinare,'" in ji shi.
"Ka sani, akwai abubuwa da yawa da suka fi samun lambar zinariya a gasar Olympics muhimmanci.
Robbie ne yanzu zinariyar Olympics".
Ɗanta yana da sunan mahaifinsa wanda ya mutu a shekara ta 2011 yana ɗan shekara 40 bayan an gano cewa yana da ciwon daji a kwakwalwa.
Daley ya ce mahaifinsa bai tabbata cewa yana mutuwa ba kuma ya yi tambaya game da tikitin zuwa London a 2012 - saboda yana son zama a gaban.
Sai ya ce: "Da ma ban gaya muku ba, cewa ba za ku iya zama a gidan Ubana ba?
"Na riƙe hannunsa har sai da ya mutu, kuma har sai da ya mutu, na san cewa za a iya cin nasara a kansu".
A shekara ta gaba, Daley ta yi tsere a gasar Olympics ta 2012 kuma ta ci tagulla.
"Na san cewa wannan shi ne burina na dukan rayuwata - na yi wa jama'a wa'azi a filin wasa na Olympics, babu abin da ya fi wannan", in ji ta.
Saboda haka, ya zaɓi waƙar da ta fi so - Proud na Heather Small - wadda ta sa shi baƙin ciki sosai sa'ad da yake shirin halartar gasar Olympics.
Ana nuna shirin Desert Island Discs a kai a kai a kan BBC Radio 4 a ranar Lahadi da ƙarfe 11:15 na yamma.
